feat(currency): centralize formatting with locale-aware compact notation

Replace ~20 duplicated inline formatting patterns and 3 hand-rolled
_formatCurrency() methods with a single formatCents() utility.

Key changes:
- New lib/core/utils/currency_formatter.dart with formatCents() that:
  - Uses NumberFormat from intl for locale-aware grouping separators
  - Switches to compact notation ($1.2M) for values greater than or equal to $1M
  - Supports all 4 currencies (USD $, EUR euro, HTG G suffix, CAD $)
  - Handles sign display (+/- for transactions, - for negatives)
  - Respects decimal overrides (0 decimals for LIMIT/AVAIL displays)
- Migrated 10 feature files: dashboard_screen, budget_screen,
  transactions_screen, accounts_screen, reports_screen, upcoming_screen,
  bill_plan_detail_screen, mark_paid_sheet, allocation_bottom_sheet,
  new_transaction_screen
- New unit tests at test/core/utils/currency_formatter_test.dart

